## Agent Memory

Shared memory file for both Cursor and Claude Code agents. When you encounter a mistake that could recur, or learn something important about this project, append it to this file under the relevant heading below. Keep entries concise. Remove entries that turn out to be wrong or outdated.

**At the end of every task session, update this file** with any new learnings before your final response. Don't ask — just do it. If nothing was learned, skip silently.

### Project structure
- Root **`.eleventyignore`** excludes templates from the build (e.g. `src/style-exercise.njk` while that URL is retired).
- Eleventy (11ty) personal blog with Nunjucks templates
- Agent instructions live in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (Cursor) and `CLAUDE.md` (Claude Code)
- CLAUDE.md uses `@` imports to pull in cursor rules and docs — avoids duplication
- Docs: `docs/commands.md`, `docs/authoring.md`, `docs/tests.md`, `docs/ideas.md`; exploration write-ups: `docs/color-theme-exploration.md` & `docs/font-stack-exploration.md` each have a **Companion tooling** section; quick links under Maintenance in `docs/commands.md`
- `docs/ideas.md` is the task tracker — has Selected, Future, Maybe Don't, and Done sections (mostly plain bullets; occasional `**REMINDER (YYYY-MM-DD)**` rows in Done)
- Eleventy config is modularized in `eleventy/config/` (filters, plugins, events, etc.) and `eleventy/utils/` (markdown, date, CSS utilities)
- `eleventy/config/transforms.js` is intentionally empty — figure wrapping moved to markdown-it plugin at parse time
- Cross-document view transitions: `@view-transition { navigation: auto; }` in `src/assets/css/jonplummer.css`; `navigation: none` under `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`. **`/color/`** loads **`color-gallery-embed.css`** after **`jonplummer.css`**; **`SITE_EMBED_EXTRA_CSS`** appends **`@view-transition { navigation: none; }`** so leaving the heavy embed uses a normal navigation (Chrome was unreliable for utility links like **`/type/`**). **`.utility-sibling-nav`** uses **`position: relative; z-index: 2`** so links stay above the embed if paint order overlaps.

### Command relationships
- `deploy` runs: `changelog` → `generate-og-images` → `test markdown` → `test frontmatter` → `build` → `test og-images` → rsync → IndexNow; if changelog changed, deploy then commits and pushes it (skipped with `--dry-run`). **rsync** must not **`--exclude=color/`** — **`/color/`** is a normal output directory (an old exclude caused live **404** while **`/type/`** / **`/ogimages/`** still deployed).
- `import-links` is a manual pre-commit step, not part of deploy — run it before building/committing so links can be reviewed and tested locally
- `test fast` runs 13 tests (`wisdom` validates `src/_data/wisdom-entries.yaml`); `test all` adds `a11y`. **`test frontmatter`** parses **`src/_posts/*.md`** with **gray-matter** (matches Eleventy); **`parseFrontMatter()`** in **`frontmatter-utils.js`** remains regex-based for scripts/tests that only need `---` … `---` splitting.
- Collected wisdom: `src/_data/wisdom-entries.yaml` + `wisdom.js` + `wisdom-build.js` + `wisdom-entries-path.js` (same folder as `links.yaml`; YAML basename ≠ `wisdom` so no merge clash with `wisdom.js`). Pagination needs `wisdom` in `getGlobalData()` — not `eleventyComputed` (runs too late). Pages `/wisdom/` and `/wisdom/tags/<tag>/`, RSS `/wisdom-feed.xml`, head link in `head/wisdom-feed.njk`; `markdown` filter renders block markdown from YAML; list UI uses `_includes/components/wisdom_entry.njk` (`footer` + `section`, same article grid as blog index; `article.wisdom-entry` skips the title row)
- `dev` auto-generates OG images on file save via `eleventy.beforeWatch`
- `validate` is shortcut for `test html`

### Workflow preferences
- **Stylelint**: `pnpm run lint:css` or `pnpm run test css`; config `.stylelintrc.json` (extends standard; several rules off for this stylesheet — see `docs/tests.md`). `scripts/test/css.js` uses `runTest`/`outputAndExit` like spell; maps Stylelint warnings to `line`/`column`/`ruleId`/`helpUrl` for `formatVerbose`. Included in `test fast`.
- **`test:changed` caveat**: `pnpm run test:changed` can report no markdown/YAML changes when edits are untracked (not yet committed), so run `pnpm run test fast` before committing new content files.
- **Color combo contrast badges**: `/color/` variant-combo cards (B&W/DR/wild/terminal) must update badge text/class on `<select>` change using per-variant `worstLcSrgb`/`worstLcP3`; static initial badge values can drift from the visible preview.
- **Harmony lab header badge**: **`renderHarmonyLabCard`** in **`generate-gallery.js`** — badge should state recipe count and that **L/C** come from the **APCA-tuned** export (≥ **`MIN_LC`** **Lc at build**); avoid vague “nudged build” alone (lede covers interactive controls).
- **Harmony lab (color-gallery)**: **Hue wheel disk** uses **`colorWheelDiskBackground()`** — **`oklch(L C Hdeg)`** conic (fixed L/C, **25** stops 0…360 in 15° steps) so disk angles match **OKLCH** marker dots and previews; an **`hsl()`** disk misaligns ~10–20° at the same nominal hue. Do not use only **`oklch(L C 0deg)` → `oklch(L C 360deg)`** without **`longer hue` / many stops**: browsers can take the **zero-length hue arc** and the ring looks **flat**. Markers are **white-filled** **`#fff`** with token-based outline shadow (no chroma fill); **`.color-wheel-dot--primary`** on hub / hue-preview; **`.color-wheel-dot--multi`** when harmony has **>3** distinct hues. **Hue wheel** `.color-wheel` must not use **`width: min(5.75rem, 100%)`** inside the embed **`hue-rotate-bar-grid` / `harmony-lab-top`** grid **`auto`** column — cyclic `%` makes intrinsic min-content **0** (wheel invisible). Use **`clamp(4rem, 28vw, 5.75rem)`** (or other definite lengths). Inline `linkDeltas` in `generate-gallery.js` must stay aligned with `buildHarmonySchemes` `pair(...)` offsets — recipe math is duplicated for the browser; **`markerHueDegrees`** (harmony hue-wheel dots) must stay aligned with the same **`linkDeltas`** cases. `tuningSlidersForRecipe` / `[data-harmony-tuning]` wrappers hide analogous / split / skew unless that recipe uses them. Harmony: **recipe** `<select>` uses **`aria-label`** only (no visible Recipe label). **Hue + tuning sliders** use visible **`<label for=…>`**. **`.harmony-lab-tuning-row[hidden]`** needs **`display: none !important`** so gallery `display:flex` does not defeat the **`hidden`** attribute. **`.harmony-lab-inline`** / **`.hue-rotate-inline`** use **`grid-template-columns: 1fr auto`** so range tracks share width. **`.harmony-lab-top`** is a **three-column** grid (**wheel · recipe · hue rotation**; collapses **42rem**). Hue reference: **`hue-rotate-bar-grid`** (**OKLCH conic** wheel + **`.hue-rotate-stack`**); wheel dot tracks **preview rotation** degrees (slider), not a single parsed theme hue.
- **Skewed split complementary tuning**: For `harmony-skewed-split-complementary`, `splitSpread (S)` controls arm separation and `harmonySkew (K)` shifts both arms together (`+hk` on both sides), not inward/outward (`+/-hk`). `K` is now treated as direct degrees (`hk = K`, no `/2`), so slider value matches perceived skew magnitude. Keep build-time `pair(...)` math and runtime `linkDeltas(...)` in sync.
- **Gallery caret sizing + token summary label**: In generated `color-gallery-embed.css`, shared details/summary carets (`.gallery-section-summary::before` + `.tokens summary::before`) use a **masked SVG right triangle** (same approach as `misc.jonplummer.com` lister) with whole-pixel box sizing (**`10px × 10px`**) and center pivot (`transform-origin: 50% 50%`). This avoids clip-path aliasing artifacts while keeping clean rotate-open behavior. Token disclosure summary text in the embed is **`View CSS tokens`**.
- **CSS token preview wrapping**: `.color-gallery-embed .code` now wraps long token lines (`white-space: pre-wrap` + `overflow-wrap: anywhere`) so the View CSS tokens panel is readable without horizontal scrolling.
- **Color gallery wild pack**: `buildWildThemes` cycles **10** solid OKLCH recipes (`i % 10`); live gallery wraps them in **`wild-combo`** (one preview pair + scheme `<select>`, same JS shape as B&W/DR). Gradients not in tokens — site uses `background-color: var(--token)`; mesh/linear gradients would need gallery-only `background` CSS or non-token layers. **Terminal-inspired**: **`terminal-combo`** (one card + select), same pattern.
- **Color gallery live `/color/`**: Interactive JS ships as **`/assets/js/color-gallery-embed.js`** (generated next to the embed partial). Apache **CSP** used to block the old **inline** `<script>` (**`script-src 'self'`**). Previews and controls also need **`style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'`**: gallery tokens live in **`style=""`** on **`.theme-root`** and in **`setAttribute('style', …)`**; without **`unsafe-inline`** on **style-src**, browsers ignore those (light/dark look identical; controls seem dead). Static hosting is fine — adjust **`.htaccess`** CSP, not app code. Dev server usually omits CSP.
