- `generate-og-images.js` has its own Nunjucks env with inline `postDate` — it runs outside Eleventy so needs its own renderer. `extractCssCustomProperties` is now shared from `eleventy/utils/css-utils.js`.
- Shared PDF conversion functions live in `scripts/utils/pdf-utils.js`
- **Presentation-to-portfolio (2026-03)**: Notes from `.pptx` (python-pptx); slide images from PDF via `pdf-utils`/Poppler. Google: Drive API export PDF + PPTX (personal OAuth first). Microsoft: Graph download PPTX + scripted PDF export with **Office on Mac** (LibreOffice optional fallback). One-shot CLI args enough; optional batch list (URLs + local paths). Checklist and next steps: `docs/ideas.md` (Selected → Portfolio).
