### Gotchas

- **`body > main`** already sets **`max-width: var(--max-width)`** and **`padding: var(--gutter)`** — inner wrappers on utility pages (e.g. **`.type-tool-page`**, **`.preview-container`**) should not repeat horizontal gutter + max-width or content looks narrower than **`/changelog/`** / **`/technologies/`**. **`/type/`** font card: avoid extra horizontal **`padding`** on **`.font-tool-card`** / **`.tool-controls`** so text lines up with the page **`h1`** like **`/color/`**.
- **`/type/`**, **`/color/`**, **`/ogimages/`** use **`tags: page`** without **`eleventyExcludeFromCollections`** (same as **`/changelog`** / **`/technologies`**) — in **`collections.page`** and **`sitemap.xml`**; **`/feed.xml`** still posts-only. **`scripts/test/seo-meta.js`** **`EXCLUDED_SHORT_TITLES`** includes **`/type`**, **`/color`**, **`/ogimages`** for intentional short slash **`<title>`** text like **`/changelog`**.
- **Color gallery embed + watch** — **`runColorGalleryBuild({ stableWildThemes: true })`** from **`eleventy.before`** (see **`eleventy/config/events.js`**): wild pack used **`Math.random`** so **`writeTextFileIfChanged`** rewrote **`color-gallery-embed-inner.html`** every build → Eleventy **`--watch`** loop. **`createStableRng`** + **`stableWildThemes`** fixes that; **`pnpm run color-gallery`** CLI still uses **`mathRnd`** for varied wild output.
- `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files have YAML frontmatter (globs, alwaysApply) that Claude Code ignores — content is still valid markdown after the frontmatter
- **Portfolio import**: `pnpm run convert-presentation` (PDF + `.pptx` → notes via `extract-pptx-notes.py` + python-pptx); `convert-pdf-with-notes` for hand-authored notes. See `docs/commands.md` § PDF page conversion; `docs/authoring.md` § Converting a PDF.
- **Date handling is load-bearing** — `addDateParsing` (timezone-aware) + permalink generation preserve WordPress-era URLs. Do not simplify without verifying every URL remains unchanged.
- Figure captions use the convention: image line immediately followed by `*caption text*` (no blank line). The `markdown-it-figure` plugin in `eleventy/utils/markdown-it-figure.js` handles this at parse time.
- Redirects: add entries to `src/_data/redirects.yaml` — the `src/.htaccess.njk` template renders them automatically via the data cascade. No separate script needed.
- **Eleventy image transform wraps `<img>` in `<picture>`** — when a parent element becomes a CSS grid container, `<picture>` is the grid item, not `<img>`. Target `> picture` for grid placement (e.g., `grid-column: 1 / -1`).
- **Spaces in asset filenames** break markdown link parsing (markdown-it doesn't recognize them as URLs) AND the Eleventy dev server's passthrough mode. Use kebab-case for all asset filenames.
- **Dark mode uses `light-dark()`** — colors are defined once in `:root` with `light-dark(lightVal, darkVal)`. Don't add a separate `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block; add new colors using the same pattern.
- **`scripts/test/color-contrast.js` parses `:root` `light-dark()`** — raw hex or `oklch(...)`; **`scripts/utils/apca-dual.js`** computes Lc on **sRGB** and **Display P3** gamut maps (`sRGBtoY` / `displayP3toY`). **Pass/fail** uses sRGB only; warnings for P3 below min while sRGB passes or ΔLc≥4 while sRGB≥min. Gallery **`themes.json`**: **`worstLcSrgb`** / **`worstLcP3`**. Extend parsing if new color syntax appears in `jonplummer.css`.
- **`docs/archive/accessibility-test-limitations.md` is historical** — a11y (`accessibility.js`) disables axe `color-contrast` on purpose; token/APCA checks are `pnpm run test color-contrast` (in `test fast`). Archive “fix axe timing” items largely superseded unless re-enabling axe contrast is desired.
- **Do not rename `wisdom-entries.yaml` → `wisdom.yaml`** while `wisdom.js` exists — both would map to global `wisdom` and raw YAML overwrites built `entries`.
- **Wisdom entry slugs are optional** — `eleventy/utils/wisdom-build.js` derives stable hash-based ids from `body` when `slug` is missing, and `scripts/test/wisdom-yaml.js` only validates `slug` when provided.
- **Wisdom YAML can break when multiline markdown is serialized as plain inline `body:` strings** — keep wisdom `body` content in block scalar style (`|-`/`|`) when rewriting to avoid mapping/indentation parse errors. Block lines must be indented **more** than the `body:` line (e.g. two extra spaces); same indentation as `body:` is invalid YAML.
- **Shortcuts: Notes folder export** — Inside **Repeat with Each**, actions (e.g. **Make Markdown from Note**) must take **`Repeat Item`**, not the **Find Notes** output variable (often also labeled **Note**). Using the find output inside the loop triggers **Choose item** with **Done** disabled.
- **`mergePostsAndLinks` needs `pageNumber === 0` for “page 1” behavior** — only then does it prepend links dated after the newest post. `src/links-feed.njk` must pass `0` (e.g. `mergePostsAndLinks(links, 0)`); otherwise the feed drops newer links and looks frozen at the latest post date.
- **OG image generation** — Recurses `src/**/*.njk` (excludes `_posts`/`_includes`/`_data`/`assets`). Skips `pagination:` templates (one file → many URLs; use shared `ogImage` like `index.png`). `ogImage: auto` must not trigger perpetual regen: `needsRegeneration` ignores `auto` for path comparison. Deploy OG line uses `filesUpdated` for “unchanged”; ℹ️ only when `ogImage` was absent in front matter but the PNG file already existed. **PNG basename rules**: **`scripts/utils/og-image-filename.js`** (required from **`generate-og-images.js`**). **`/ogimages/`** grid sort: **`scripts/utils/og-image-gallery-sort.js`** uses front-matter **`date`**, then **`YYYY-MM-DD-`** parse from post-style filenames, then PNG **`mtime`**.
- **GitHub push + Dependabot `remote:` line** — On `git push`, GitHub may print `GitHub found N vulnerability…` with a Dependabot link. **Not controllable from this repo** (no git hook or config disables it). Security / Dependabot can already show **Fixed** while that line still appears until alerts are dismissed or GitHub rescans. **Agents**: after a successful push, do not repeat or escalate that footer as a new action item unless the user asks for a security review.
- **`@11ty/eleventy-plugin-rss` v3** — ESM-only (`export default`); `require("@11ty/eleventy-plugin-rss")` fails. Use `await import("@11ty/eleventy-plugin-rss")` and `addPlugin(rssModule.default)`; root `.eleventy.js` must be `async` and `await configurePlugins(...)`.
- **`cspell` 10.x** — Declares `engines.node: >=22.18.0`; root `package.json` includes matching `engines` so installs match spell tooling. `cspell.json` / `spell.js` unchanged for this bump.
- **`@xmldom/xmldom` 0.9.x** — Used only in `scripts/test/rss-feed.js` (`DOMParser`); `require()` still works; bump is `package.json` + lockfile.
- **`markdownlint-cli2` 0.22.x** — Invoked from `scripts/test/markdown.js` with `.markdownlint.json`; 0.20→0.22 needed no config or script changes here.
- **Stale `_site/` paths** — After removing or renaming templates, Eleventy may not delete old HTML under `_site/`; SEO/OG tests then fail on orphans (e.g. former `_site/type/gallery/`). Remove the stale directory or wipe `_site` before `pnpm run test fast`.

### What worked
- Parallel agents work well for independent code changes (e.g., two unrelated simplifications at once)
- modern-css.com is a good reference for identifying CSS modernization opportunities
